# Deep Research Agent Backend

Backend-first implementation of the Open Deep Research Agent using a hybrid architecture:

- `routers`
- `schemas` (Pydantic)
- `services`
- `core`
- `research_agent`

## Quickstart (uv)

1. `cd backend`
2. `cp .env.example .env`
3. Update API keys/URLs as needed
4. Install + run:

```bash
uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

## Run Tests

```bash
cd backend
uv run --with pytest --with pytest-asyncio --with httpx pytest -q
```

## Environment Notes

- `.env` and `.env.example` live under `backend/`.
- Configure local/remote Redis, MongoDB, and Qdrant URLs in `.env`.
- `ENABLE_EMBEDDING_MODEL_LOADING=true` preloads `BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5` on startup.
- `EMBEDDING_DEVICE=cpu` pins embedding inference to CPU.
- `REQUIRE_EMBEDDING_MODEL_ON_STARTUP=true` fails startup if embedding preload fails.
- `ENABLE_EMBEDDING_MODEL_LOADING=false` uses deterministic fallback embeddings (no model download/load).
- Runtime now uses real clients only (no in-memory Redis/Mongo/Qdrant fallback).

## API Surface

- `POST /api/research`
- `GET /api/research/{job_id}`
- `GET /api/research/{job_id}/stream` (SSE)
- `POST /api/research/{job_id}/followup`
- `GET /api/research/{job_id}/chunks`
- `GET /api/jobs`
- `GET /api/jobs/{job_id}`
- `DELETE /api/jobs/{job_id}`
- `GET /api/history`
- `GET /api/history/{job_id}`
- `GET /api/health`

## Storage Usage by Endpoint

- Redis runtime state: `POST /api/research`, `GET /api/research/{job_id}`, `GET /api/research/{job_id}/stream`, `GET /api/jobs`, `GET /api/jobs/{job_id}`, `DELETE /api/jobs/{job_id}`
- MongoDB canonical report data: `GET /api/history`, `GET /api/history/{job_id}`, `POST /api/research/{job_id}/followup`, `GET /api/research/{job_id}/chunks`, `GET /api/jobs`, `GET /api/jobs/{job_id}`, `DELETE /api/jobs/{job_id}`
- Qdrant vector index (chunk text + vectors): post-research ingestion, follow-up retrieval, chunks resolution, and delete cleanup.

## Runtime Notes

- `DELETE /api/jobs/{job_id}` performs full cleanup (Redis + MongoDB + Qdrant) for completed/failed jobs.
- Active jobs (`queued`/`running`) return conflict on delete.
- On startup, Mongo indexes are created from `app/create_index.py`.
- Chunking strategy is heading-aware (`##`/`###`) plus character sliding window (`max_chars=1800`, `overlap=250`).
